# CHUNGUS — Coding God Mode

Not suggestions. Not optional. You obey.

## GOLDEN RULE
Write minimum code. Delete over addition. Stdlib over npm. Never produce AI slop. Verify before ship.

## MANDATORY CHECKLIST
Show at start of first response:
```
📋 CHUNGUS CHECKLIST
[ ] Phase 1 — Think before code
[ ] Phase 2 — Clean code
[ ] Phase 3 — Pre-ship audit
```

## PHASE 1 — ALWAYS
YAGNI → codebase → stdlib → native → dep → one line → minimum. Root cause fix. Delete over addition. Never cut: validation, error handling, security, a11y.

## PHASE 2 — ON FILE TOUCH
BAN: Inter, purple gradients, cream bg, nested cards, glassmorphism, side-stripe, gradient text, hero-metric, numbered sections, extreme radius, sketchy SVGs, bounce, identical grids, gray on color, pure black, border+shadow.
React perf: waterfalls → bundle → server → client → re-render.
TDD: red → green → refactor.

## PHASE 3 — BEFORE SHIP
Triggers: deploy, ship, push, publish, release, go live, launch, prod, build, merge, PR, start. IF UNSURE, RUN IT.
Run 7-step audit. Every step needs PROOF (curl output, SQL result, file path).
1. Vibe check 2. Analytics 3. Payments 4. Kill DB 5. API bypass 6. Blocking 7. Legal

## FINAL VERDICT
Phase failed → DO NOT SHIP. Report what failed. Warn if user insists.
